    • Constructor Detail

      • TrapezoidalMotionProfile

        public TrapezoidalMotionProfile​(double maxAcceleration,
                                double maxVelocity,
                                double setpoint)
        Creates a TrapezoidalMotionProfile

        This motion profile is without a specified start point, meaning the setpoint is in relative position.

        Parameters:
        maxAcceleration - maximum acceleration
        maxVelocity - maximum velocity
        setpoint - distance traveled

      • TrapezoidalMotionProfile

        public TrapezoidalMotionProfile​(double maxAcceleration,
                                double maxVelocity,
                                double startPoint,
                                double setpoint)
        Creates a TrapezoidalMotionProfile

        This motion profile is with a start point, meaning the setpoint is in world position

        Parameters:
        maxAcceleration - maximum acceleration
        maxVelocity - maximum velocity
        startPoint - the starting point of the motion profile.
        setpoint - distance traveled

      • TrapezoidalMotionProfile

        public TrapezoidalMotionProfile​(double maxAcceleration,
                                double maxVelocity,
                                double setpoint,
                                boolean reversed)
        Creates a TrapezoidalMotionProfile

        Reversed is normally automatically calculated, but there is an option to manually specify it if needed.

        Parameters:
        maxAcceleration - maximum acceleration
        maxVelocity - maximum velocity
        setpoint - distance traveled
        reversed - whether or not the position output should be negative, resulting in a reversed movement

      • TrapezoidalMotionProfile

        public TrapezoidalMotionProfile​(double maxAcceleration,
                                double maxVelocity,
                                double startPoint,
                                double setpoint,
                                boolean reversed)
        Creates a TrapezoidalMotionProfile

        Reversed is normally automatically calculated, but there is an option to manually specify it if needed.

        Parameters:
        maxAcceleration - maximum acceleration
        maxVelocity - maximum velocity
        setpoint - distance traveled
        startPoint - starting position of the mechanism (current position when initiating the motion profile)
        reversed - whether or not the position output should be negative, resulting in a reversed movement
